<h1>Problem 1369 - 2006 IMOSL, N3, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>We define a sequence \(\left(a_{1},a_{2},a_{3},\ldots \right)\) by
\[a_{n} = \frac {1}{n}\left(\left\lfloor\frac {n}{1}\right\rfloor + \left\lfloor\frac {n}{2}\right\rfloor + \cdots + \left\lfloor\frac {n}{n}\right\rfloor\right),\] where \(\lfloor x\rfloor\) denotes the integer part of \(x\).</p>
<p><ol><li>Prove that \(a_{n+1} > a_n\) infinitely often.</li><li>Prove that \(a_{n+1} < a_n\) infinitely often.</li></ol></p>
